gmd:dataQualityInfo.gmd:DQ_DataQuality.gmd:lineage.gmd:LI_Lineage.gmd:statement.gco:CharacterString.#text:§Functional traits were mesured in different campaigns by the ECOPAR (Comparative Ecology) research team, CEFE (Center for Functional and Evolutive Ecology, Montpellier, France). Contributors to these measurements include: Adeline Fayolle, Ignacio Pérez-Ramos, Iris Bumb, Jules Segrestin, Karim Barkaoui, and Maud Bernard-Verdier. Trait measurements were performed according to standardized methodologies described in: Pérez-Harguindeguy, N., Díaz, S., Garnier, E., Lavorel, S., Poorter, H., Jaureguiberry, P., Bret-Harte, M. S., Cornwell, W. K., Craine, J. M., Gurvich, D. E., Urcelay, C., Veneklaas, E. J., Reich, P. B., Poorter, L., Wright, I. J., Ray, P., Enrico, L., Pausas, J. G., de Vos, A. C., … Cornelissen, J. H. C. (2013). New handbook for standardised measurement of plant functional traits worldwide. Australian Journal of Botany, 61(3), 167. https://doi.org/10.1071/BT12225, and according to standardized ontologies, described in: Garnier, E., Stahl, U., Laporte, M.-A., Kattge, J., Mougenot, I., Kühn, I., Laporte, B., Amiaud, B., Ahrestani, F. S., Bönisch, G., Bunker, D. E., Cornelissen, J. H. C., Díaz, S., Enquist, B. J., Gachet, S., Jaureguiberry, P., Kleyer, M., Lavorel, S., Maicher, L., … Klotz, S. (2017). Towards a thesaurus of plant characteristics: An ecological contribution. Journal of Ecology, 105(2), 298–309. https://doi.org/10.1111/1365-2745.12698. Data were check for outliers in unvariate trait distribution across and within species, as well as on bivariate relationships well described previously in the literature. Consistencies across years of measurements were also checked. 
Abundance data were measured by Maud Bernad-Verdier in the extensive management regime (Bernard-Verdier, M., Navas, M.-L., Vellend, M., Violle, C., Fayolle, A., & Garnier, E. (2012). Community assembly along a soil depth gradient: Contrasting patterns of plant trait convergence and divergence in a Mediterranean rangeland. Journal of Ecology, 100(6), 1422–1433. https://doi.org/10.1111/1365-2745.12003), and come from long-term monitoring in the intensive regime. The latter was supervised by Daniel Hubert and Didier Alard. Finally, environmental data was taken from Chollet, S., Rambal, S., Fayolle, A., Hubert, D., Foulquié, D., & Garnier, E. (2014). Combined effects of climate, resource availability, and plant traits on biomass produced in a Mediterranean rangeland. Ecology, 95(3), 737–748. https://doi.org/10.1890/13-0751.1.
